FIXES APPLIED:
==============

1. TORCH PLACEMENT - Simplified
   BEFORE: Used LightPlacementEngine which disabled itself when TorchPool found
   AFTER:  Use SpatialPlacer.PlaceTorches() directly
   
   PlaceTorchesSimple():
   - Gets SpatialPlacer component
   - Enables PlaceTorchesEnabled = true
   - Calls PlaceTorches() directly
   - No complex LightPlacementEngine logic

2. PLAYER SPAWN - Auto-create if missing
   BEFORE: Only logged error if PlayerController not found
   AFTER:  Creates a player capsule if not found
   
   PlacePlayerAtSpawn():
   - Tries to find PlayerController
   - If not found: creates capsule primitive at spawn position
   - If found: teleports to entrance room or default position
   - Always ensures player exists in scene

3. OUTER WALLS - Simplified spawning
   BEFORE: Verbose debug logging for each wall
   AFTER:  Concise logging, same functionality
   
   SpawnWalls():
   - Removed excessive debug logs
   - Kept outer wall spawning logic intact
   - Single summary log at end

4. DEBUG LOGS - Reduced verbosity
   BEFORE: 10+ lines of wall spawn logs
   AFTER:  1 summary line
   
   Console output now shows:
   - Ground floor spawn (1 line)
   - Ceiling spawn (1 line)
   - Walls spawn (1 line summary)
   - Torches placed (1 line)
   - Player spawn (1 line)

